  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 560 mg
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Peel @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce}, then cut into ½-inch cubes. Place in a #medium pot{} with @salt{pinch} and enough water to cover by 1 inch. Bring to a boil and cook until easily pierced by a knife, ~{12-15%minutes}. Drain and return to pot.

Use a #mallet{} or heavy #pan{} to crush @Tricolor Peppercorns{1/4%teaspoon} in their bag until coarsely ground. Finely chop @Parsley{1/4%ounce}. Peel, halve, and chop @Shallot{1}. Toss @Green Beans{6%ounce}, a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%tablespoon}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} on a #baking sheet{}. Roast in oven until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat @Rib-Eye Steak{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add to pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside to rest.

> TIP: Loosely cover steak with aluminum foil to keep it warm.

Reduce heat under pan to medium-low and add a drizzle of oil. Add shallot and cook, tossing, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in ¼ tsp crushed peppercorns (use more or less to taste), @Beef Demi-Glace{1}, and @water{1/2%cup}. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer until reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat. Add @Butter{1%tablespoon} and half the @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}. Stir until butter is melted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add remaining sour cream and @Truffle Oil{1/2%teaspoon} to pot with drained potatoes (we sent extra oil—use more or less to taste). Mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until smooth. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Add a splash of milk to make potatoes extra creamy.

Thinly slice steak against the grain. Toss green beans with @Almonds{1%ounce}. Divide mashed potatoes, green beans, and steak between plates. Drizzle sauce over steak and potatoes. Garnish with parsley.